                        "displayName": "Jochen Ott",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "I did not find any other issues down the road, i.e. writing out parquet files with \"write_statistics=False\" works with unaligned buffers. Having said that, I would not be surprised\u00a0 if there are more latent bugs similar to that (i.e. UB due to unaligned access on code-level that do not manifest because current compilers emit instructions that work even for unaligned data). To catch those, I think a code-level review of all the reinterpret_casts or array access would probably the best way to catch those.",
